 is used as a basis to simulate the behaviour of Interspersing Express Traffic
 (IET) in the form of MAC Merge Frames (mFrames) in function of time.
 As simulation environment OMNeT++ is used, a discrete event simulation
 environment for communication networks.
 The results of the present work reveal the impacts on delay times of Ethernet
 frames in due consideration of different rule sets and varied data traffic
 in a HSR ring.
 Moreover there is put a spotlight on the factors such as data backlog in
 view of various dataflow rules of particular HSR nodes and how many Ethernet
 frames that are being preempted at a time during one simulation run.
